{{Unreferenced|date=June 2007}} {{Infobox video game | title = The Amazing Spider-Man 2 | collapsible = | state = | image = The Amazing Spider-Man 2 Coverart.png | caption = North American box art | developer = [[Bits Studios]] | publisher = [[Acclaim Entertainment]]{{efn|Released under the [[LJN]] brand name.}} | platforms = [[Game Boy]] | released = {{vgrelease|EU|1992|NA|August 1992}} | genre = [[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]] | modes = [[Single player video game|Single-player]] | composer = }}
'''''The Amazing Spider-Man 2''''' (released as '''''Spider-Man 2''''' in North America) is a [[Game Boy]] [[video game]] released by [[Acclaim Entertainment]] in 1992. It was programmed by [[Bits Studios]].
==Gameplay== The game is different from the original ''[[The Amazing Spider-Man (handheld video game)|The Amazing Spider-Man]]'' game, in that along with its [[Action-adventure game|action-adventure]] theme, [[Spider-Man]] also has to collect various objects located in each level in order to solve puzzles.
==Plot== A collection of supervillains (the [[Hobgoblin (comics)|Hobgoblin]], [[Lizard (comics)|Lizard]], [[Graviton (comics)|Graviton]], [[Carnage (comics)|Carnage]], and [[Mysterio]]) have framed Spider-Man for a bank robbery. He must survive several side-scrolling levels, battling various thugs and supervillains in order to clear his name.
